E005.description: An uprising took place in Karelia. According to the Cheka, a trace of Finland was noticed in the uprising.
E005.title: Karelian uprising

E011.description: Apparently, the Italians are beginning to recognize our power rather than the power of the Entente's henchmen. This is our chance to persuade them to withdraw their troops in exchange for possible concessions.
E011.description1: You have started the process of negotiations with Italy
E011.title: Italian-Turkish talks

E010.description: British and Americans have drawn up an agreement that will ease our lot by changing the order of payments so that we can pay them, and they will also be able to persuade Paris to withdraw its troops from the Rhine.
E010.title: Ruhr Conflict

E001.answer1: Perhaps it is worth making peace!
E001.answer2: Flame of revolution will not be extinguished!
E001.description: Our forces are exhausted, and the front has grown into a trench war. The enemy offers to conclude peace on the current borders on the condition that we pay reparations. What should we do?
E001.description1: You signed a peace treaty and agreed to pay reparations
E001.title: Soviet-Polish War

E008.description: Germany was unable to pay the reparations specified in the Treaty of Versailles, against this background, France occupied the Ruhr region in Germany.
E008.description1: Your diplomats, together with American diplomats, are trying to resolve this conflict
E008.title: Ruhr Conflict

E002.description: Our troops were able to throw the enemy back to the original border, the front grew into a positional war, the conflict is reaching a deadlock. Maybe we should make peace with the enemy?
E002.description1: You are proposing a peace treaty to the Bolsheviks
E002.title: Soviet-Polish War

E016.description: The government of Central Lithuania - the Vilnius Seimas, openly declared the entry of their state into our state.
E016.title: Request from Central Lithuania

E006.answer1: Need to put pressure on them!
E006.description: Germany does not pay the full amount of reparations imposed by her in the Treaty of Versailles. What should we do?
E006.description1: Your troops occupy the right-bank part of the Ruhr industrial region
E006.title: Non-payment of reparations

E015.description: The French reneged on our agreement and annexed the Rhineland.
E015.description1: You sanctioned France for its expansionism
E015.title: Ruhr Conflict

E013.description: The Italians have agreed to our agreement and are now withdrawing their troops from Anatolia.
E013.title: Withdrawal of Italian troops

E007.answer1: Expansion of Entente will not be allowed!
E007.description: Due to the inability to pay us huge reparations, French troops occupied the industrial zone of the Ruhr
E007.description1: You protested to the Entente countries for the occupation of the Ruhr region
E007.title: Ruhr Conflict

E012.answer2: This offer is't profitable for us!
E012.description: The new government in Turkey offers us a deal - we withdraw troops from Anatolia, and they recognize the islands and Libya for us, as well as improved relations.
E012.description1: You agreed to Turkey's proposal and began the process of withdrawing troops from Anatolia
E012.description2: You did not agree with Turkey's proposal
E012.title: Italian-Turkish talks

E014.answer1: We will pay, and French will regret it!
E014.description: The British and the Americans have drawn up an agreement that changes the way reparations are paid so that we can pay them. They also tried to persuade France to withdraw its troops from the Rhine, but they annexed the Rhineland.
E014.title: Ruhr Conflict

E004.description: According to our intelligence, the population of Karelia is dissatisfied with the policy of Soviet Russia. This can play into our hands and weaken Russia by sponsoring local separatists there.
E004.description1: You sponsored an uprising in Karelia
E004.title: Karelian adventure

E009.answer1: We will have to sign an agreement.
E009.answer2: We will not sign, Rhine is ours!
E009.description: British and American diplomats are proposing to change the order of reparations payments so that Germany can pay them, and we are being offered to withdraw troops from Germany, otherwise there will be problems.
E009.description1: You signed the Anglo-American agreement and began the process of withdrawing troops from the Rhine
E009.description2: You refuse to sign the Anglo-American agreement and decide to annex the Rhineland occupied by your troops
E009.title: Ruhr Conflict

E003.description: We managed to make peace with the Bolsheviks and they agreed to pay us reparations.
E003.description1: You have received reparations from Soviet Russia
E003.title: Soviet-Polish War

E017.description: Our troops occupied Istanbul, the Entente lackeys fell. Each time we are getting closer and closer to the independence of the Turkish state!
E017.title: Capture of Istanbul

Anarcho-capitalist Commune of the Tambov Krai
